{"TopicId":115700,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.6.1] NodeHelper - tool used to edit node positions","CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-07-12T06:21:10Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T18:19:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I have it fixed. Any requests for this while I am coding today?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T22:37:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnone here. Very helpful little utility - in fact missed it sorely when I went in to edit some node positions a few days ago and actually just said \u0022screw it for now, hope NodeHelper is updated soon!\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T23:21:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222551143\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462040378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think I have it fixed. Any requests for this while I am coding today?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLovely :3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI might have some requests, would you please make a prerelease version?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-30T23:21:54Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2016 11:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Enceos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-30T23:28:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m making a bunch of changes that make it better for how I use it, and hopefully how others use it too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I am having an issue with the nodes appearing \u0022behind\u0022 the model.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XNWnOK3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/XNWnOK3.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lextacy","CreatedById":107955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T00:51:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni only say please include the ability to change nodes in VAB graphically so I can visualize the change of the node in VAB.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T04:14:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222551782\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462058882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m making a bunch of changes that make it better for how I use it, and hopefully how others use it too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I am having an issue with the nodes appearing \u0022behind\u0022 the model.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKIS also had this issue, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155445\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155445-igorz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@IgorZ\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0has\u00A0solved it by increasing the renderQueue number. You can view the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/KospY/KIS/issues/121\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eissue\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E and the \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/KospY/KIS/commit/4187eaa84f759f35f903860d9a845ef7a24f44ee\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Efix\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E on Github.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for the features, I agree with lextacy,\u00A0I wonder if\u00A0it is possible at all to give the nodes those dragging arrows which we use for offsetting parts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-01T04:44:07Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2016 04:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 1, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Enceos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T13:07:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s probably doable, but probably a bit of work and I am checking\u00A0for small things\u00A0I can do for now since Ares and Alexandria are waiting for me to start them up\u00A0again. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I also already simplified the node UI a little so I\u0027m going to see how much that helps me/us first. I like the idea a lot though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for the render queue I had already tried it and it did not help. I think the issue is I need to\u00A0make my models on the root part. That might be a bit of work.\u00A0If I change the layer it also helps a little but creates a different problem of not being able\u00A0to see the exact intersection point of the node with the part models.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-01T13:10:18Z\u0022 title=\u002205/01/2016 01:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 1, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Felbourn\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T21:23:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t get the balls to intersect. I can get them \u0022behind\u0022 the part like the first image I posted. I can get them \u0022in front\u0022 like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022yfOeq3v.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/yfOeq3v.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut of course what we really want is for them to intersect like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022R95BUY8.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/R95BUY8.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T21:39:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anyone wants to play with this prerelease in 1.1.1 KSP then here you go:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Felbourn/NodeHelper/releases/tag/1.1.1.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Felbourn/NodeHelper/releases/tag/1.1.1.0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T04:24:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222553966\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462137787\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t get the balls to intersect. I can get them \u0022behind\u0022 the part like the first image I posted. I can get them \u0022in front\u0022 like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut of course what we really want is for them to intersect like this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe we should try pinging the knowledgeable guys? \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97344-felbourn/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002297344\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97344-felbourn/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Felbourn\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Would you\u00A0please remove Blizzy\u0027s Toolbar as dependency? )\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NathanKell","CreatedById":75006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T04:40:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110725-enceos/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110725\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110725-enceos/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Enceos\u003C/a\u003E he already did. I got nuthin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T05:31:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho uses mods but does not use toolbar? That\u0027s crazy talk! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s almost like saying you don\u0027t have module manager installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Enceos","CreatedById":110725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T08:57:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222554856\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462167071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWho uses mods but does not use toolbar? That\u0027s crazy talk! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s almost like saying you don\u0027t have module manager installed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be nice if it could work as well independently :3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot many mods have buttons in VAB, stock toolbar has plenty of space there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-02T09:20:57Z\u0022 title=\u002205/02/2016 09:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 2, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Enceos\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lextacy","CreatedById":107955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T10:37:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntried the 1.1 release. GOod stuff here. My wish come true about the node changes being visible in VAB. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan I make another recommendation? \u00A0What is holding back the ability to have the new node creations being saved to the original parts .cfg? \u00A0Id like to have the change be \u0022live\u0022 without having to do a \u0022MMreloadCache\u0022 \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso a bit of an anoyance \u00A0: \u00A0The gui goes away constantly when you mouse around in VAB. It acts exacty if the way the stock\u00A0right-click part menus work. Could you make it so the node helpers gui sticks in the air?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T10:41:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222554997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462179474\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould be nice if it could work as well independently :3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot many mods have buttons in VAB, stock toolbar has plenty of space there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my gaming install (as opposed to the dev install) I have 9 mods which put buttons on the toolbar. \u00A0So far I haven\u0027t run out of space, but only because I\u0027ve combined 4 \u00A0mods into one in EditorExtensionsRedux\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222554780\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462163043\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Enceos\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Enceos said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe we should try pinging the knowledgeable guys? \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow! \u00A0It\u0027s gratifying that you said that, thanks. \u00A0Unfortunately, I don\u0027t have a clue. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T15:48:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222555095\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462185465\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lextacy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, lextacy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnew node creations being saved to the original parts .cfg\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a good idea to alter the original files provided by Squad or a mod maker. The files might become corrupted or break saves. Or a bug in my mod might ruin the originals by mistake. You also can\u0027t install a newer version without losing prior changes.\u00A0You should be using Module Manager patches to create new parts, or at least use patches to affect existing ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI cannot reproduce the GUI going away by moving the mouse. For me the appropriate\u00A0windows are available when they should be.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lextacy","CreatedById":107955,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T21:34:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222555701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462204136\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a good idea to alter the original files provided by Squad or a mod maker. The files might become corrupted or break saves. Or a bug in my mod might ruin the originals by mistake. You also can\u0027t install a newer version without losing prior changes.\u00A0You should be using Module Manager patches to create new parts, or at least use patches to affect existing ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI cannot reproduce the GUI going away by moving the mouse. For me the appropriate\u00A0windows are available when they should be.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh good point. Well patches arent gonna hurt I guess \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can reproduce the \u0022bug\u0022 of the menus disappearing by right-clicking to camera pan around your craft in VAB.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alewx","CreatedById":102791,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T21:56:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222555701\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462204136\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a good idea to alter the original files provided by Squad or a mod maker. The files might become corrupted or break saves. Or a bug in my mod might ruin the originals by mistake. You also can\u0027t install a newer version without losing prior changes.\u00A0You should be using Module Manager patches to create new parts, or at least use patches to affect existing ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI cannot reproduce the GUI going away by moving the mouse. For me the appropriate\u00A0windows are available when they should be.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut maybe it could write a MM patch file that will provide the made changed with the next Startup of the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-03T00:47:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222556755\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462226168\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022102791\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alewx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Alewx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe it could write a MM patch file\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea I\u00A0was thinking the same thing, though it also feels like one of those yak-shaving kinds\u00A0of tasks. It\u0027ll never be as easy as it seems on paper. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alewx","CreatedById":102791,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-03T07:41:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222557219\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462236427\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea I\u00A0was thinking the same thing, though it also feels like one of those yak-shaving kinds\u00A0of tasks. It\u0027ll never be as easy as it seems on paper. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIsn\u0027t that the usual case \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBTW I noticed that the new version for 1.1 does not contain CIT, did you change nodehelper to be standalone?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-03T15:01:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222557828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462261278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022102791\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Alewx\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Alewx said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndid you change nodehelper to be standalone?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not have the source code to CIT so I faked it by writing new functions of my own to replace anything that would\u00A0not compile without his library.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222556676\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462224847\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lextacy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, lextacy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nright-clicking to camera pan around your craft in VAB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s actually how I use the VAB by default. I do that all the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Alewx","CreatedById":102791,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-03T15:05:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222558431\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022115700\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462287717\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002297344\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Felbourn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Felbourn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not have the source code to CIT so I faked it by writing new functions of my own to replace anything that would\u00A0not compile without his library.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI test it as soon as I\u0027m back home.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T19:50:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97344-felbourn/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002297344\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97344-felbourn/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Felbourn\u003C/a\u003Ei noticed that there is not a finer step value than 0.01 units yet frequently some parts require for the nodes to be aligned within 0.001 units. Would be possible to add another button for the \u00220.001\u0022 stepping?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Felbourn","CreatedById":97344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T20:35:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do a lot of part editing and never needed more than 0.01 myself which is why I did not clutter my UI with more. I can make that an option, but\u00A0until then you can still set a custom 0.001 the old way. Edit the text field and hit Set.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-06T08:32:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97344-felbourn/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002297344\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/97344-felbourn/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Felbourn\u003C/a\u003EOh. I asked for the button because when i tried to enter a numeric value directly it did not accept it and i assumed that it is used only for displaying purposes now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}